Package de.boereck.matcher

This is the root package for the Case Matcher library.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    NoResultCaseMatcher<I>
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given object and define associated actions that are executed when a case matches for the given object.
    NoResultDoubleCaseMatcher
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given double value and define associated actions that are executed when a case matches for the given value.
    NoResultIntCaseMatcher
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given int value and define associated actions that are executed when a case matches for the given value.
    NoResultLongCaseMatcher
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given long value and define associated actions that are executed when a case matches for the given value.
    ResultCaseMatcher<I,O>
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given object and define associated functions that are executed when a case matches for the given object and return a result value.
    ResultDoubleCaseMatcher<O>
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given double value and define associated functions that are executed when a case matches for the given value and return a result object.
    ResultIntCaseMatcher<O>
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given int value and define associated functions that are executed when a case matches for the given value and return a result object.
    ResultLongCaseMatcher<O>
    This interface is used to define cases that can be used to found a given long value and define associated functions that are executed when a case matches for the given value and return a result object.

Package de.boereck.matcher Description

This is the root package for the Case Matcher library. This package provides the basic interfaces for defining cases. To create eager versions of case matchers, the class EagerMatcher provides static methods. Other implementations of these interfaces (such as lazy or asynchronous versions) are possible, but not part of this core library.
See Also:
EagerMatcher
